messages.message: For the build app, when it automatically finds the class and fields, it does not show the provenance of the created field in the document which makes it hard for users to see where its getting this information from
This also happens after building the app and viewing results for a new file
we may or may not get provenance back for  each field so it is possible in this case the model didn’t return a provenance
if you’re able to look at the network request and verify that would be helpful
followed up with udit here, looks like model is not returning provenance cc @Eric Han
After looking at network-requests, it seems that run_sync is not returning a provenance for the fields like arjun said. Response is empty for provenance
:+1: makes sense, i’ll close the ticket as provenance is being tracked in a different place for model dev team. Marking this as resolved for now
